What I've learned during this pandemic? That the swedish government and majority of the swedish population doesn't give a shit about anything or anyone but themselves. Especially older people. I've lost count on how many times I've had elderly people stand right next to me, or even coughing right at me. I'm pregnant, and a health care worker, and i do as much as i can to stay protected. No one is wearing a mask, people are going to parties, hanging out in massive gatherings etc... So yeah. We haven't even had a lockdown, everything is open, and people don't care.

What I have learnt from lockdown is that I dont need people as much as I thought. I have however also cried more than ever either from missing my exams or just missing people as well as being fed up with my family. I have also learnt that I am more creative than I thought.
